# Sample kernel log for trying oom-tui without waiting for a real OOM kill:
#
#     cargo run -- --file examples/sample-oom.log
#
# Contains three incidents that exercise different parser paths:
#   1. A global (host-wide) kill, with a full task dump and Mem-Info block.
#   2. A Kubernetes container kill against a cgroup memory limit.
#   3. An old-kernel syslog-format line with no pgtables: field.
#
# Process names and pod IDs are fictional.

